lenders.name: brands
lenders.occupational_info:
Acuity Brands introduces ROAM, its new revolutionary streetlight monitoring system that delivers high energy savings and reduced maintenance costs. ROAM represents a complete transformation in how street lighting and other outdoor lighting systems are monitored and maintained. It enables proactive and efficient resolution of issues and errors the minute it occurs – eliminating the need for citizens to report or complain. 
ROAM functions by utilizing an intelligent photocontrol with an embedded communication chip for each light fixture. This allows the fixture to report attributes errors and location for easy monitoring. Once installed, these photo controls can communicate with other photo controls, essentially creating a mesh network. This results in a self-configuring and self-healing outdoor wireless light control system.
ROAM has already reduced streetlight outages in some areas for up to 90%. It has also cut street lighting energy costs and carbon emissions by half. This translates to a big improvement in customer satisfaction and in revenue generation. ROAM makes streetlight monitoring so easy yet so effective for municipalities and utilities.

lenders.name: MPUS
lenders.loan_because: MPUS is a organization for disable people. MPUS was established in 2006 as a participatory which was designed to have implementation for development concept of the disabled poor community of the country. MPUS has been a growing force in developing of Bangladesh urban and rural disabled people through direct field operation and as a voluntary resource organization for the provision support services. MPUS is a non-political, non-profitable & non-government voluntary-welfare & development organization.
lenders.occupational_info:
MPUS Goal is to improve the ultimate socio-economic condition of the Socially Extremely Excluded, Marginal & vulnerable disabled people & to ensure t heir equal rights & opportunities for participation in the mainstream development. 

Disabled people of the society are socially extremely excluded, marginal & vulnerable. They are deprived basic needs, fundamental rights, health, sanitation & environmental service & also exploiting in various ways. In this situation MPUS mission is to develop & co-operative with them to develop their overall socio-economic completions. 

The vision of “Mukti Probandhi Unnayan Sangstha (MPUS)”, Naogoan, Bangladesh is to create an environment based on unity, discipline and co-operation and utilizing those through the initiatives towards various social developments and to accelerate it through undertaking different socio-economic project activating for helpless and unemployed disabled people with a special attention for women and children.
